PAM-olive is an independent open-source project. Third-party names and marks
remain the property of their respective owners.

The project implements publicly documented privileged-access-management
concepts without including proprietary source code.

The web interface includes a vendored copy of htmx under the Zero-Clause BSD
license. Its license is reproduced next to the vendored asset under
static/vendor/htmx/LICENSE.

The SSH terminal includes a vendored copy of xterm.js 6.0.0 under the MIT
license. Its license is reproduced next to the vendored asset under
static/vendor/xterm/LICENSE.

The Docker Compose deployment can run the official Apache Guacamole 1.6.0
client and guacd container images, distributed separately under the Apache
License 2.0. No Apache Guacamole source code is vendored in this repository.
